The 18-year-old girl&#8217;s naked and mutilated body was discovered on a field in Valhalla Park in September. CAPE TOWN - The trial of a man accused of killing and mutilating 18-year-old Lekita Moore in Valhalla Park in September will get underway in February.Cameron Wilson appeared in the Western Cape High Court for a pre-trial hearing on Thursday.Wilson allegedly stabbed the teenager nearly a hundred times.He allegedly stabbed the deceased and cut her genitals.The 19-year-old appeared before Judge Robert Henney on Thursday, when a trial date was set for 13 February 2017.Valhalla Park residents found the 18-year-old teenager's body on a field in Nooitgedacht in September.She had attended a karaoke party in the area the night before.Wilson also faces unrelated charges of attempted murder and murder, dating back to 2014.#TeenMurder Valhalla Park residents say their community is still in mourning. LI pic.twitter.com/aCYgtbn36S(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)